Earth to Aybolit!  They aren't allowed to buy &quot;wtf they want&quot;, that's the whole <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>point</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of sanctions.  And here's the rub- black market profits amount to a trickle of what Iraq needs in terms of imports.  Food and water alone costs an arid country half the size of Iraq 2 billion dollars a year.  Industrial upkeep and maintenance investment for a country that size costs 9-12 billion dollars a year.  Like it or not- there is no way Iraq can scrape that kind of money up.  It certainly isn't enough for a weapon's programme (irrelevant in any case, since containment &amp; deterrence work).<br>
