<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;We should be able to punish corporate leaders who are convicted of abusing their powers.  By banning them from ever serving again as officers or directors of a publicly held corporation.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
George Bush actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>said</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that, and he should know I suppose, because hes been arrested 3 times for different offences, and only got off with an $800,000 oil shares trading charge when the investigator, appointed by his <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>father</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> said there was insufficient evidence to proceed.  Quel suprise? <br>
<br>
Wow, not a bad job there- and that only took me 15 minutes.  Goodness knows what I'd find in another 10 or so- I think I've made my point as far as political corruption goes.<br>
<br>
Finally:<br>
You seem to have the courage of your convictions in backing this war Kad, but I have yet to hear your reasoning for why war is needed now.<br>
<br>
Bottom line:  If containment has failed, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>prove it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
                  If deterrence is failing, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>prove it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
               <br>
In the absence of proving either of these, there isn't even the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>beginnnings</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of a case for war.  He's playing for time- time to do what if he's contained?  He's deceiving- to what end, if he's being deterred?  He's not telling the truth- what politican isn't economical with the truth?  <br>
<br>
There isn't a proven case for war Kad- give me a case for war and I can begin to argue its efficacy- in the absence of that, supporters of the war have no argument for supporting it.  Suspicion, hatred, fear, conjecture, bloodlust, hatred for &quot;A-rabs&quot; or &quot;rag-heads&quot;, those aren't a case for war, none of them are.  Speculation is no basis for committing troops Kad, surely someone with a military background can appreciate that reasoning?  Only with properly gathered intelligence and clear proof of an imminent threat should forces be committed.  Of course, if you think it's civilized to target &quot;suspected&quot; terrorists and &quot;suspected&quot; purveyors of WMD, why not take that one step further and convict &quot;suspected&quot; criminals?  Oh yeah, there's that little thing called due process isn't there...<br>
<br>
Here's the irony- the lowest of low scumbags being tried for murder with intent- even he needs a case to be built before a conviction can even be considered.  Where's your case Kad?  Or do you think your suspicions and conjectures plus those of your government is a strong enough case for war?  The floor's all yours Kad- tell me why you think there's a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>proven</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> case for going to war.  Because if there is proof that the current measures aren't good enough to see off a potential threat...I sure as hell can't see it.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Taranna Dhossarim<br>
